Ri repeated well-known North Korean complaints about Washington's opposition to gradual nuclear disarmament, where North Korea is rewarded for gradual disarmament steps, but his declaration was significant because it did not reject unilateral nuclear disarmament completely, as Pyongyang has done in the past.
Ri referred to a joint statement by Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump issued in Singapore on June 12, at the very first meeting between a sitting President of the United States and a North Korean leader, in which Kim pledged to work towards "nuclear disarmament of the Korean Peninsula," while Trump guaranteed North Korea's security.
