He said, “To this day, it is these feelings of being inferior and different that have been the real motivation and have me the power and strength to succeed.”
He wanted to prove that he “was something,” he said, so he didn’t disappoint everyone when they finally found out about his sexuality.
He is a two-time bronze medalist in the Olympics and has become a high-profile LGBT ambassador. He used his participation at this year's Commonwealth Delegate in Australia to appeal for more countries to decriminalise homosexuality.
He said he stands up because he feels lucky to be able to live openly without negative consequences and wants to give others “hope.”
